And I think you agreed and you said basically a lot of the things you and I were talking about, you agreed.

2562
03:15:14,530 --> 03:15:17,252
One big issue, the appeal process.

2563
03:15:17,352 --> 03:15:18,113
And what did you say?

2564
03:15:18,173 --> 03:15:18,914
Correct me if I'm wrong.

2565
03:15:18,954 --> 03:15:19,694
I'll paraphrase you.

2566
03:15:20,175 --> 03:15:24,619
You said, if there was one thing you oppressed upon the mayor, keep it out of city hall, get an outside independent person.

2567
03:15:26,000 --> 03:15:26,561
That's what you said.

2568
03:15:30,749 --> 03:15:32,490
Dan Nash, Regional Manager of Public Parking.

2569
03:15:33,091 --> 03:15:45,478
One of the things that we had suggested was to provide administrative hearing through our office to try to weed out some of the appeals that may come through that could be administered prior to going to City Hall.

2570
03:15:45,518 --> 03:15:53,083
But at no point were we anticipating removing anyone, the final administrative hearing process or the hearing process from City Hall.

2571
03:15:53,123 --> 03:15:54,244
That was never on the table.

2572
03:15:54,704 --> 03:15:59,767
No, you indicated at that point in time, it would be wise and advisable to hire an outside independent person

2573
03:16:00,191 --> 03:16:04,112
That way there would be no conflict as it relates to the parking ticket and city hall.

2574
03:16:04,392 --> 03:16:20,658
But what I talked to you about is something that we had done in Springfield, Mass, where we had hired a outside attorney to come in and administrative hearings, uh, through the office to try to take care of some of the burden that might be left on the city's actual appeal process.

2575
03:16:20,738 --> 03:16:25,179
So your recommendation is almost the same, whether it be Springfield and Medford or what have you.

2576
03:16:25,439 --> 03:16:26,940
Why should Medford be any different than Springfield?

2577
03:16:28,862 --> 03:16:29,923
I think every city's different.

2578
03:16:30,363 --> 03:16:31,143
Springfield's huge.

2579
03:16:31,904 --> 03:16:41,810
And I think part of that and discussions with the administration is to allow the process to go see what happens.

2580
03:16:41,890 --> 03:16:47,814
I think the chief explained it very well just briefly is we know that the first couple of months there will probably be an influx in appeals.

2581
03:16:48,334 --> 03:16:54,578
And if we see that that number is not dwindling down, then there are options that we could put into place to help assist with the appeal process.

2582
03:16:55,879 --> 03:16:57,780
Well, I think that's something that should have been discussed

2583
03:16:58,292 --> 03:17:10,939
and finalized and included in the contract, but just for the type of terminology that you're saying, that if in fact it gets to a point in time, as Councilor Moxley alluded to, and then an outside independent person needs to come in if they want to start off small, but the mayor was adamant.

2584
03:17:11,439 --> 03:17:17,322
So if the mayor is going to be that adamant that Diane McLeod is a lovely person, she does her job, she has a full-time job to do.

2585
03:17:17,963 --> 03:17:23,686
So I don't know how she's going to be able to pick up and chief, even though you said she may get all the technological thing, it might go up to a hundred.

2586
03:17:23,746 --> 03:17:25,687
I mean, a hundred appeals is a hundred appeals.

2587
03:17:25,707 --> 03:17:27,848
That's a lot to take care of during a period of time.

2588
03:17:28,407 --> 03:17:35,572
But all I know is this, that if I was a contributor to the mayor of this community, and I wound up getting a ticket, I'd be knocking on his door and saying, hey, what's this all about?

2589
03:17:35,832 --> 03:17:37,533
Oh, you're not going to get another contribution from me.

2590
03:17:38,133 --> 03:17:40,235
Because he kept it here in City Hall, which is wrong.

2591
03:17:40,815 --> 03:17:41,836
It should be out of City Hall.

2592
03:17:42,096 --> 03:17:46,899
If this program really wanted to work its way right, it would be completely independent to anything that's political.

2593
03:17:47,419 --> 03:17:51,402
And if you have to work out these little things, Councilor Camuso, I probably agree with you in one thing.

2594
03:17:52,142 --> 03:17:52,662
And that's this.

2595
03:17:53,183 --> 03:17:53,303
Yeah.

2596
03:17:53,628 --> 03:17:55,309
on this particular thing, and I think it's a big one.

2597
03:17:55,389 --> 03:18:07,839
I think if you were going to put meters in the city, you should have put meters so everybody that drove up would have seen them, they would have been able to understand it, the signage would have said how long you could have stayed, and this would have relieved an awful lot, an awful lot of the grief that's here.

2598
03:18:08,185 --> 03:18:10,486
But your inconsistencies are all over the city.

2599
03:18:10,506 --> 03:18:14,667
I'm not saying you, because you guys are only doing as you said where the mayor told you to do.

2600
03:18:15,187 --> 03:18:30,873
I don't understand how you can go down Main Street from Medford Square to South Medford and have blocks of stores, have nothing at all, and then go to West Medford where there are kiosks, go to Haines Square where there are kiosks, and then Haines Square, at the end of Haines Square come to Medford Square,

2601
03:18:31,363 --> 03:18:36,447
as Mr. Dobbs indicated, have had the same blocks of stores, like businesses, not having anything.

2602
03:18:37,047 --> 03:18:45,313
And if you're going to say you're going to roll it out further, there's another phase to this, that means there's going to be more anguish and more heartache to the people in this community.

2603
03:18:46,133 --> 03:18:47,314
We're not Newbury Street.

2604
03:18:47,354 --> 03:18:49,295
We don't have to get up at 7 o'clock in the morning.

2605
03:18:49,476 --> 03:18:59,603
And Newbury Street in Boston is the only place where they did this experiment with the kiosk, because the other parts of Boston still have the, and Brookline, who had the kiosk, got rid of it, because it was damning to the business community out there.

2606
03:19:00,183 --> 03:19:01,544
We're not one of these communities.

2607
03:19:01,785 --> 03:19:03,086
We're a simple little community.

2608
03:19:03,786 --> 03:19:04,827
Point of information.

2609
03:19:05,768 --> 03:19:15,778
Councillor Knight.

2610
03:19:15,818 --> 03:19:19,221
Canal Street, Friend Street, Portland Street, they all have kiosks.

2611
03:19:19,521 --> 03:19:20,282
It's not station.

2612
03:19:20,342 --> 03:19:21,483
It's not downtown Boston.

2613
03:19:22,782 --> 03:19:31,031
A number of different communities in New York City, New York State, California, Los Angeles County, they have kiosks.

2614
03:19:31,211 --> 03:19:36,157
I think that they're new, they're scary, but at the end of the day, we're going to be able to figure it out.

2615
03:19:36,177 --> 03:19:38,059
I don't think that we're giving the public enough credit.

2616
03:19:38,439 --> 03:19:41,842
in terms of their ability to adapt to new technology.

2617
03:19:41,903 --> 03:19:42,463
We've all done it.

2618
03:19:42,743 --> 03:19:47,368
We've seen people come along and be able to work computers like wizards after a couple of weeks.

2619
03:19:47,748 --> 03:19:48,469
It is what it is.

2620
03:19:48,529 --> 03:19:56,977
I think that, you know, we're in a situation right now where we can go and we can talk about the past and we can talk about what happened, or we can look forward to see, all right, these are coming in.

2621
03:19:57,217 --> 03:19:58,018
What's the process?

2622
03:19:58,078 --> 03:20:00,920
How are we going to deal with our griefs and our gripes and our grievances?

2623
03:20:01,381 --> 03:20:03,583
And in order for us to move forward,

2624
03:20:03,906 --> 03:20:06,549
I think we really need to look at the plan and say the plan's in place.

2625
03:20:07,310 --> 03:20:09,012
These are the, these are the recourses that we have.

2626
03:20:09,353 --> 03:20:10,534
The traffic commission governs.

2627
03:20:11,195 --> 03:20:14,158
We have the traffic commission and we go to the traffic commission.

2628
03:20:14,439 --> 03:20:15,119
That's the process.

2629
03:20:15,139 --> 03:20:16,181
There's a process in place.

2630
03:20:16,221 --> 03:20:24,050
Now we can talk about the process that didn't happen to get us to where we are, or we can look forward and we can say, this is the process that we need to take in order to make this a successful plan.

2631
03:20:24,544 --> 03:20:26,446
And that's where I am with this, Mr. President.

2632
03:20:26,726 --> 03:20:29,309
I think that, you know, the history is the history.

2633
03:20:29,369 --> 03:20:30,270
We all know what we voted for.

2634
03:20:30,550 --> 03:20:33,373
We voted to give the mayor the authority to enter into a contract for 10 years.

2635
03:20:33,434 --> 03:20:34,034
That's what we did.

2636
03:20:34,375 --> 03:20:36,197
And we allowed him to go to the table and negotiate.

2637
03:20:36,537 --> 03:20:39,060
He went to the table, he negotiated, and this is what he came back with.

2638
03:20:39,520 --> 03:20:40,341
We have our concerns.

2639
03:20:40,381 --> 03:20:41,242
We all have our concerns.

2640
03:20:41,262 --> 03:20:45,807
And we've all had individual conversations with the chief and with the people from Republic and with the administration.

2641
03:20:46,167 --> 03:20:57,974
But I think that right now, for the people out there that have concerns and that are scared and that are worried about what's going to happen, we need to tell them what the process is and provide them with an avenue to get answers to have their concerns addressed.

2642
03:20:58,314 --> 03:21:04,357
Because in my experiences so far, I've gotten a number of calls about people that had issues about loading zones, and loading zones have been made.

2643
03:21:05,117 --> 03:21:11,941
The folks from Republic have been pretty reasonable in terms of making accommodations to make this program and plan work for them.

2644
03:21:13,802 --> 03:21:25,329
If we're going to roll out a plan that's going to be successful and that people are going to buy into, we need to look at the future and what avenues we have in order to address problems, not the past and what didn't happen and what should have.

2645
03:21:25,830 --> 03:21:27,611
Thank you, Counselor, for your point of information.

2646
03:21:27,631 --> 03:21:31,013
Counselor Penta has the floor.

2647
03:21:31,133 --> 03:21:35,676
I disagree extremely with Counselor Knight on this because the past is the leader of the future.

2648
03:21:35,916 --> 03:21:38,898
And if you can't learn from the past, the future will never have any value.

2649
03:21:39,429 --> 03:21:40,711
The fact of the matter is this.

2650
03:21:41,091 --> 03:21:42,073
There was no process.

2651
03:21:42,133 --> 03:21:42,914
It never took place.

2652
03:21:43,194 --> 03:21:45,397
And every time you keep saying, well, we have no recourse.

2653
03:21:45,417 --> 03:21:46,078
Let's go forward.

2654
03:21:46,118 --> 03:21:48,141
How can you go forward when you don't even know what took place?

2655
03:21:48,382 --> 03:21:52,187
Because you weren't a part of it, when you were asked to be a part of it, when you were told to be a part of it.

2656
03:21:52,568 --> 03:21:54,791
And you never voted for the finalization of the contract.

2657
03:21:54,991 --> 03:21:56,072
The man took it upon himself.

2658
03:21:58,343 --> 03:22:01,745
The bottom line to this whole thing is that there's a whole bunch of issues here.

2659
03:22:02,065 --> 03:22:04,206
You guys are only here for one reason, that's to make money.

2660
03:22:04,246 --> 03:22:07,688
You're not here to help the city of Medford, you're here to get your salary and to make money.

2661
03:22:07,948 --> 03:22:13,471
So as far as that concern, you should probably sit down because the real questions that need to be asked, the mayor, he's the one that should be here.

2662
03:22:13,711 --> 03:22:16,952
He's the one that should be explaining all of this to the people that's going on.

2663
03:22:18,093 --> 03:22:19,814
So let me ask you something, sir.

2664
03:22:20,694 --> 03:22:23,476
Well, I'm gonna ask him something, he wants to stay there.

2665
03:22:24,438 --> 03:22:25,759
I like him, he's a nice guy.

2666
03:22:26,359 --> 03:22:27,199
Let me ask you something.

2667
03:22:27,379 --> 03:22:27,519
Yes.

2668
03:22:27,939 --> 03:22:30,500
I have pictures here of you people bolting signs to trees.

2669
03:22:30,520 --> 03:22:31,941
Why did you bolt the signs to the trees?

2670
03:22:32,961 --> 03:22:33,821
Were you told to do that?

2671
03:22:34,742 --> 03:22:35,242
No, we were not.

2672
03:22:35,442 --> 03:22:36,482
Did you do it yourself?

2673
03:22:36,502 --> 03:22:43,905
The signs that you see there, you know, what we did is we went along with what we had seen throughout the city, which were signs on trees.

2674
03:22:43,945 --> 03:22:45,766
That's one I think is right out in front of Amici's.

2675
03:22:46,206 --> 03:22:51,528
There was a one hour parking sign that was bolted to that tree that we took down and put back up.

2676
03:22:51,833 --> 03:22:53,294
Well, what about the signs in Haines Square?

2677
03:22:53,875 --> 03:22:54,856
There was nothing on those trees.

2678
03:22:54,976 --> 03:22:55,757
We made a mistake.

2679
03:22:56,357 --> 03:22:58,039
I personally made a mistake because I told the staff.

2680
03:22:58,059 --> 03:23:00,801
Well, didn't the mayor give you any instructions not to bolt signs on trees?

2681
03:23:00,821 --> 03:23:01,702
Did anybody tell you that?

2682
03:23:01,882 --> 03:23:03,043
It's against the ordinance to do that.

2683
03:23:03,824 --> 03:23:05,185
It was my fault for not checking the ordinance.

2684
03:23:05,205 --> 03:23:07,727
No, did anybody tell you if you're going to put the signs up?

2685
03:23:07,747 --> 03:23:09,289
Point of information, Mr. President.

2686
03:23:09,309 --> 03:23:10,570
Point of information, Counselor Camuto.

2687
03:23:10,590 --> 03:23:11,631
Either yes or no.

2688
03:23:11,671 --> 03:23:18,237
Not to throw this gentleman under the bus, but normal person says you don't put the sign on the tree.

2689
03:23:19,768 --> 03:23:22,150
I mean, the guy's acknowledging he made a mistake.

2690
03:23:22,250 --> 03:23:22,951
You want to beat him up?

2691
03:23:22,991 --> 03:23:23,551
Who didn't tell him?

2692
03:23:23,571 --> 03:23:24,372
The chief, the police?

2693
03:23:24,392 --> 03:23:25,513
Yeah, because it's important.

2694
03:23:25,553 --> 03:23:26,854
It's part of what this process is all about.

2695
03:23:26,874 --> 03:23:27,614
I understand, counselor.

2696
03:23:27,795 --> 03:23:29,376
But did you lock your car when you come in tonight?

2697
03:23:29,516 --> 03:23:29,796
Yes, I did.

2698
03:23:29,816 --> 03:23:30,497
Did you lock your car?

2699
03:23:30,637 --> 03:23:31,077
Yes, I did.

2700
03:23:31,357 --> 03:23:35,060
I mean, we're going volley here on ridiculous stuff now.

2701
03:23:35,080 --> 03:23:36,001
Well, that's in your mind.

2702
03:23:36,402 --> 03:23:37,122
No, that's in your mind.

2703
03:23:37,142 --> 03:23:38,964
That's why your mind and mine is entirely different.

2704
03:23:38,984 --> 03:23:39,544
That's correct.

2705
03:23:39,584 --> 03:23:40,004
Thank God.

2706
03:23:40,385 --> 03:23:41,526
I have a pitch, counselor.

2707
03:23:41,826 --> 03:23:42,286
I have a pitch.

2708
03:23:42,306 --> 03:23:43,187
Just answer your question.

2709
03:23:44,658 --> 03:23:49,661
The gentleman did answer the question, and we want to avoid a prosecutorial tone.

2710
03:23:49,681 --> 03:23:51,142
We're not prosecuting anybody.

2711
03:23:51,702 --> 03:23:53,503
Counselor Camuso, point of information.

2712
03:23:53,543 --> 03:23:57,906
To follow up on that, Aggie Tudin was very, very helpful in straightening the situation out.

2713
03:23:58,046 --> 03:24:00,127
So kudos to her.

2714
03:24:00,528 --> 03:24:02,849
I'm not sure if she actually talked to you or someone in your office.

2715
03:24:02,869 --> 03:24:04,690
She's our tree warden here and arborist.

2716
03:24:05,431 --> 03:24:06,491
And she was very concerned.

2717
03:24:08,351 --> 03:24:09,713
She took the bull by the horns on that.

2718
03:24:09,733 --> 03:24:10,954
Thank you, Councilor Camuso.

2719
03:24:13,257 --> 03:24:14,839
Followed by Councilor Caravaglio.

2720
03:24:14,939 --> 03:24:16,542
Point of information, Councilor Knight.

2721
03:24:18,164 --> 03:24:21,127
Personally, I don't feel as though Republic should be putting up any signs, Mr. President.

2722
03:24:21,328 --> 03:24:23,651
And the reason so is because that work is DPW work.

2723
03:24:23,691 --> 03:24:25,353
And we have a gentleman in the sign shop.

2724
03:24:25,793 --> 03:24:28,575
who has a job, and his job is to be in charge of the signs.

2725
03:24:28,995 --> 03:24:36,559
So this subletting of work that should be done by the DBW, I feel as though is a problem, Mr. President.

2726
03:24:36,619 --> 03:24:38,319
I think that this work should be handled internally.

2727
03:24:38,359 --> 03:24:44,583
We have a sign shop, we have a gentleman that's in charge of signs, and we have a gentleman who's well versed in the ordinances in the city of Medford.

2728
03:24:44,643 --> 03:24:47,364
Quite frankly, Mr. Nash isn't from Medford, he came to this city.

2729
03:24:48,087 --> 03:24:52,310
and maybe he relied on what he saw or what he's seen in other communities, so be it.

2730
03:24:52,611 --> 03:24:58,435
But we have a sign shop, we have gentlemen in the DPW who know our ordinances, and I think that this is where the work should lie, not outside.

2731
03:24:58,455 --> 03:24:59,856
Thank you, Councilor Knight.

2732
03:24:59,916 --> 03:25:00,616
Councilor Pentez.

2733
03:25:00,676 --> 03:25:02,998
In response to Councilor Knight, that's absolutely not true.

2734
03:25:03,018 --> 03:25:08,382
If you read the contract in the IRFP, they made the commitment to put the signs up and to replace the signs that are there.

2735
03:25:08,842 --> 03:25:10,283
That's part of the contract.

2736
03:25:11,284 --> 03:25:12,705
Any information, Councilor Knight?

2737
03:25:14,909 --> 03:25:20,072
The contract that you're referring to is the contract with Republic, but the City of Medford also has a contract.

2738
03:25:20,092 --> 03:25:26,115
The contract is with the Medford DPW Association, represented by Local 25, and they have rights.

2739
03:25:26,535 --> 03:25:34,219
And if they aren't willing to sublet their work, and they haven't had an opportunity to negotiate the impact of the subletting of their work, then there's a violation.

2740
03:25:34,439 --> 03:25:36,841
Point of information, Councilor Marks.

2741
03:25:37,481 --> 03:25:39,842
So are you saying the may is in violation of the contract?

2742
03:25:41,483 --> 03:25:42,324
That's what you just stated.

2743
03:25:43,630 --> 03:25:49,791
that the union contract has been repudiated based upon the fact that outside people- So you're just stating again tonight that the may is in violation of the union contract?

2744
03:25:49,811 --> 03:25:51,052
That's my interpretation, yes.

2745
03:25:51,212 --> 03:25:51,992
That's my interpretation.

2746
03:25:52,052 --> 03:25:53,672
I believe the union contract has been repudiated.

2747
03:25:53,692 --> 03:25:55,912
The DPW workers are suitably employed.

2748
03:25:56,473 --> 03:26:08,175
Counselor Penta has- Yeah, the contract and the IRFP and the three pages of questions that were asked for which you, Republic, indicated that you folks would put up the signs and you would replace- is that true or false?

2749
03:26:08,895 --> 03:26:11,816
That you would replace and put up the signs that were existing.

2750
03:26:12,556 --> 03:26:13,416
That's part of the contract.

2751
03:26:14,100 --> 03:26:16,341
part of the contract was, yes, we were responsible.

2752
03:26:16,381 --> 03:26:17,062
Thank you very much.

2753
03:26:17,242 --> 03:26:17,602
Okay.

2754
03:26:17,862 --> 03:26:18,663
Not the city of Medford.

2755
03:26:19,103 --> 03:26:24,947
Um, we have a, I have a picture here of one of your kiosks in front of Oak Grove cemetery on the sidewalk.

2756
03:26:25,467 --> 03:26:29,490
Can you please explain in the middle of a snowstorm when they go down the street to plow the sidewalk?

2757
03:26:31,268 --> 03:26:32,749
Point of information, Mr. President.

2758
03:26:32,789 --> 03:26:34,750
Point of information, Counselor Camuso.

2759
03:26:34,790 --> 03:26:37,773
That area in particular is maintained by the Cemetery Department.

2760
03:26:38,253 --> 03:26:44,758
And they actually do that whole area, as you probably know, Counselor, from your expertise in that particular area.

2761
03:26:45,198 --> 03:26:48,300
It's done very early in the snowstorms.

2762
03:26:48,901 --> 03:26:51,182
And I'm sure it will continue to be done.

2763
03:26:52,143 --> 03:26:52,844
What expertise?

2764
03:26:52,864 --> 03:26:53,344
You do this?

2765
03:26:53,744 --> 03:26:54,825
You plow the sidewalk, Counselor?

2766
03:26:54,865 --> 03:26:55,105
No, no, no.

2767
03:26:55,145 --> 03:26:58,248
His expertise, he's up in that area a lot, given the nature of his business.

2768
03:26:58,268 --> 03:26:59,909
You do the plowing on the sidewalk, yes or no?

2769
03:27:01,333 --> 03:27:03,615
In front of Oak Grove Cemetery, do you plow the sidewalk there?

2770
03:27:03,655 --> 03:27:04,136
Yes or no?

2771
03:27:04,376 --> 03:27:05,057
